  "plainText": "Exclusive to:\nFor the filter in Don't Starve Together, see Prototypers & Stations Filter.\nTab Icon\n“I am one heck of a scientist.”\n–Wilson\nThe Science Tab allows the player to craft scientific Items and Structures. It is displayed as the Atom icon on the left-hand side of the screen.\nDownloadable Content[edit | edit source]\nIn the Reign of Giants DLC, Electrical Doodads and Ice Flingomatics were introduced to the Science Tab. They are available to craft in all DLCs.\nIn the Shipwrecked DLC, Sea Labs, Ice Maker 3000s and Quacken Drills were added to the Science Tab. Many Structures in this tab can be flooded.\nThe Hamlet DLC adds Smelters and Oscillating Fans to this tab.\nCraftable Items and Structures[edit | edit source]\nThe following items and structures can be crafted from the Science Tab:\nScience Machine\nAlchemy Engine\nDivining Rod\nThermal Measurer\nRainometer\nGunpowder\nLightning Rod\nElectrical Doodad\nIce Flingomatic\nSea Lab\nIce Maker 3000\nQuacken Drill\nSmelter\nOscillating Fan\nAccomploshrine\nConsole Editions only\nView or edit this template\nDon't Starve Crafting Tabs\nRegular\nTools\nLight\nSurvival\nFood\nScience\nFight\nStructures\nRefine\nMagic\nDress\n(Nautical )\n(Treasure Hunting )\nCharacter-Specific\nBooks\nTinkering\n(Green Thumb )\nNon-prototypable\nAncient\nVolcanic\n(Renovate\nCity Planning )",
